<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-07T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="1237" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1237">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 867.48/312</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-07T14:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 7, 1916, 2 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2814. Department’s 2784, June 24, 5 p. m. Again inform Turkish
                                Government of the great sympathy which the citizens of the United
                                States feel for the destitute in Syria, and add that a refusal of
                                the Turkish Government to give friendly consideration to this
                                Government’s suggestion regarding relief supplies for Syria will not
                                be understood in this country and might seriously affect in the
                                future the sentiments here toward the Turkish Government and Turkish
                                people.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>